<table width='95%'>
<Tr><td>
<b>Site Packaging Tool:</b>&nbsp;Creates a CSV or Excel export of products suitable for import into another
Zoovy site using the advanced CSV import tool.<br>
<br>
Export Products:<br>
<form action='index.cgi' name='selFrm' method='post'>
<input type='hidden' name='ACTION' value=''>
<input type='hidden' name='PRODUCTS' value='<!-- PRODUCTS -->'>
<table width='500'><tr><td>
<!-- PRODUCTOUT --><br>
</td></tr></table>
<!-- PRODUCT_WARNING --><br>
<input style='width: 200px; font-size: 8pt;' type='submit' value=' Select All Products ' onClick='selFrm.ACTION.value="SELECT_ALL";'><br>
<input style='width: 200px; font-size: 8pt;' type='submit' value=' Select Products Individually ' onClick='selFrm.ACTION.value="SELECT_PRODUCTS";'><br>
<input style='width: 200px; font-size: 8pt;' type='submit' value=' Select from Range of Products ' onClick='selFrm.ACTION.value="SELECT_RANGE";'><br>
<input style='width: 200px; font-size: 8pt;' type='submit' value=' Select by Navigation Categories ' onClick='selFrm.ACTION.value="SELECT_NAVCAT";'><br>
<input style='width: 200px; font-size: 8pt;' type='submit' value=' Select by Management Category ' onClick='selFrm.ACTION.value="SELECT_MANAGECAT";'><br>
</form>

<i>Note: Effective 10/23/04 - 
due to the resource intensive nature of compiling a CSV full product record exports with dynamic are limited to 500 products, 
specify fixed headers to increase this limit up to the maximum of 250,000 total data-cells.</i>
<br>
<form target="_blank" method='POST' action='index.cgi' name='myForm'>
<input type='hidden' name='ACTION' value='PACKAGE'>
<input type='hidden' name='PRODUCTS' value='<!-- PRODUCTS -->'>

Special Export Options:<br>
<input type='checkbox' name='NAVCATS'> Export Navigation Categories -- MUCH SLOWER!<br>
<input type='checkbox' name='CATEGORIES'> Export Management Categories<br>
<input type='checkbox' name='IMAGELIB'> Export Image URLs rather than Image Library names (may break Excel)<br>
<input type='hidden' name='TS' value='<!-- TS -->'> Timestamp<br>
Fields: <input type="textbox" name="FIELDS" value="<!-- FIELDS -->" size="50"><br>
NOTE: Leave "fields" blank to export a full product record with dynamic headers. 
To specify header fields, specify product attributes separated by commas, leave no whitespace 
e.g. "zoovy:prod_name,zoovy:base_price,zoovy:prod_image1" (without the quotes) - 
without specifying which fields you want to export you will be limited to 500 products per export.<br>

<P>
<br>
<b>Output Option:</b><br>
<table>
	<tr>
		<td><input style='width: 120px; font-size: 8pt;' type='submit' value=' Package as CSV File ' onClick='myForm.action = "/biz/manage/csvexport/index.cgi/<!-- USERDATE -->.csv";'></td>
		<td>For non/Microsoft applications (e.g. OpenOffice, Filemaker Pro)</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td><input style='width: 120px; font-size: 8pt;' type='submit' value=' Package for Excel ' onClick='myForm.ACTION.value="EXCEL"; myForm.action="/biz/manage/csvexport/index.cgi/<!-- USERDATE -->.xls";'></td>
		<td>For Microsoft Excel Users<br>
		<i>Due to limitations of string length this export is known not to work with Excel 5, or Excel 97 - 
Excel has a limitation of 65,536 rows (although Zoovy will export more than that)</i>
		</td>
	</tr>
